author: Gareth Davies For Mailonline
title: Saudi king takes 506 TONS of luggage for trip to Indonesia | Daily Mail Online
text: A Saudi king is taking 506 tons of luggage with him for a nine-day trip to Indonesia. Salman bin Abdulaziz al-Saud's huge haul includes two Mercedes-Benz s600 limousines and a pair of elevators. He is set to visit Indonesia tomorrow to join an enormous entourage of 620 people as well as 800 delegates, including ministers and 25 princes. Saudi Arabia's King Abdullah bin Abdulaziz al-Saud pictured back in 2012 in France Two Mercedes-Benz s600 limousines (pictured) and a pair of elevators are part of the cargo Jasa Angkasa Semesta (JAS) has been tasked with the huge operation of lugging the cargo from Saudi Arabia, and has dedicated 572 members of staff to handle it. The airfreight company's president director Adji Gunawan told Antara news agency that 63 tons would be unloaded at the Halim Perdanakusuma airport in East Jakarta and the rest would be sent to Ngurah Rai International Airport in Denpasar, Bali, according to The Jakarta Post . 'We have been officially appointed to handle all cargo belonging to the kingâ€™s entourage aircraft,' he said. It will be the first time in 46 years a Saudi king has visited Indonesia - the world's largest Muslim population. RELATED ARTICLES
